Stock market returns have averaged 16 per cent a year under the Conservatives .
The figures are a boost for David Cameron and George Osborne ahead of the general election on May 7 .
Experts warn a hung parliament could send financial markets into tailspin and the pound and shares crashing .
A survey of FTSE 100 bosses this weekend showed 70 per cent believe a Labour government would be a 'catastrophe' for the economy .